[ ] QA 05: DataTrees, Expanders, and Collectors
{@} @Local:7777<QA:Test.DataTrees:1.0.0
   [@] @Math << @Community:math<Math.Operations:1.0.0


{-} -ProcessDataTrees
   [ ] Output declarations
   (-) >processedMap##Uniform
      (>) #<ValueType << #Float
   [T] -T.CLI"ProcessDataTrees"
   [Q] -Q.Default
   [W] -W.Aljam3
   [ ]
   [ ] Initialize a Map of strings to floats using Constructor Input ($)
   [-] $prices##UniformRecord
      ($) #<ValueType << #Float
      ( ) keys in any data tree is an Enum
      ( ) No need for constructor for 
      ( ) numeric and literal strings
      ($) .AAPL << 150.0
      ($) .GOOGL << 2800.0
      ($) .MSFT << 300.0
   [ ]
   [ ] Use the unified =ForEach expander
   [=] =ForEach
      (=) <Data << $prices
      (=) >item >> $price
      (=) >key >> $ticker
      [ ]
      [ ] Mini-pipeline per key-value pair
      [-] @Math-API.Float.Multiply
         (-) <a << $price
         (-) <b << 1.1
         (-) >result >> $newPrice
            (>) >! 0.0
      [ ]
      [ ] Collect back into map using the unified *Collect
      [*] *Collect
         (*) <item << $newPrice
         (*) <key << $ticker
         (*) >Map >> >processedMap
